- <i>Well, congratulations.</i>
<i>- Excuse me?</i>

03:16.120 --> 03:19.567
<i>You're a guaranteed winner of one
of three fabulous prizes.</i>

03:19.760 --> 03:22.809
<i>- Have you won anything major before?
- No, never.</i>

03:22.960 --> 03:24.803
<i>- Well, you have now.
- Oh, my God.</i>

03:24.960 --> 03:27.088
<i>- Are you kidding?
- No, it's confirmed.</i>

03:27.240 --> 03:31.245
- Are you sure? Okay, what <i>did I win?</i>
- Either the Chevy Blazer, the Paris--

03:31.400 --> 03:35.962
<i>- Do you have</i> a water <i>filtration system?</i>
- <i>A faucet filter? No, sir. I don't.</i>

03:36.120 --> 03:39.647
- Do you read the papers or watch TV?
- Sometimes, yeah.

03:39.800 --> 03:42.610
Well, then you've probably
seen our advertisements.

03:42.760 --> 03:45.764
The government is gonna
make you pay a tax on the prize.

03:45.920 --> 03:49.766
But if you buy the Waterson 2000
water filtration system...

03:49.920 --> 03:53.970
...the prize gets recorded as a sales
expense, and you don't pay any tax.

03:54.120 --> 03:55.451
- Good deal, huh?
- Yeah.

03:55.600 --> 03:57.762
<i>- Yeah.
- And then I get the trip to Paris?</i>

03:57.960 --> 04:01.362
You're guaranteed one
of those three prizes.

04:01.520 --> 04:05.844
I'm gonna have a courier come to your
house. You're gonna give him a check.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.365
He's gonna come to me...

04:07.600 --> 04:11.650
...and we'll decide which one of those
prizes you get. See how that works?

04:11.800 --> 04:14.963
- How much do <i>I pay?</i>
- Three hundred ninety-eight dollars.

04:15.120 --> 04:18.647
<i>- You'd pay</i> twice that <i>in stores.
- I need</i> to <i>speak</i> to <i>my husband.</i>

04:18.959 --> 04:23.522
Irene, my supervisorjust stepped into my
office, and he would love to talk to you.

04:23.680 --> 04:26.968
Can you hold just a sec? Thanks, Irene.

04:27.480 --> 04:29.960
- Good morning.
- Who says so?

04:30.160 --> 04:32.481
Irene Fisk. She wants to talk
to her husband first.

04:32.640 --> 04:36.326
- John Goodhew, regional vice president.
- Oh.

04:36.480 --> 04:39.211
Congratulations.
Which prize are you hoping for?

04:39.360 --> 04:41.362
- Paris.
- That would be my choice too.

04:41.520 --> 04:44.046
- We've never been.
- My associate tells me...

04:44.200 --> 04:46.851
...you have five grandkids? Wow.

04:47.000 --> 04:50.641
I understand you'd like to speak
to your husband first about this.

04:50.800 --> 04:54.247
But the thing is, my secretary
is having a baby this afternoon.

04:54.400 --> 04:57.324
Everyone at the office is about
to head to the hospital.

04:57.520 --> 04:58.885
<i>Well, that's wonderful.</i>

04:59.040 --> 05:02.089
Let me confirm your address
for our courier service.

05:02.280 --> 05:03.611
<i>All right.</i>

05:09.440 --> 05:10.771
Hey.

05:10.920 --> 05:12.604
Sorry, sorry.

05:14.200 --> 05:16.248
Any thoughts on lunch?

05:16.760 --> 05:18.967
Spicy calamari?

05:19.120 --> 05:21.122
Thai food?

05:43.000 --> 05:46.846
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

05:47.400 --> 05:48.561
Pygmies.

05:53.280 --> 05:54.930
Otis, hush, hush.

05:58.920 --> 06:00.968
- Can I help you?
- Carolyn Schaffer?

06:01.120 --> 06:03.327
- Yes.
- I'm Agent Kellaway. This is Agent Cole.

06:03.480 --> 06:05.482
We're from
the Federal Trade Commission.

06:05.640 --> 06:08.928
Sorry to disturb you.
We'd like to ask you a few questions.

06:09.080 --> 06:11.242
- Is everything all right?
- We hope so.

06:11.400 --> 06:16.088
Mrs. Schaffer, can you tell us exactly
what the man said on the phone?

06:16.240 --> 06:19.528
He said that there'd been a contest,
and I had won a prize.

06:19.680 --> 06:22.160
There'd be a drawing next week,
and I'd win...

06:22.360 --> 06:24.966
...either a Chevy Blazer,
a diamond necklace...

06:25.120 --> 06:27.771
...or a trip to Italy or France.
I don't remember.

06:27.920 --> 06:33.290
And that if I bought one of their filtration
things, I wouldn't have to pay the tax.

06:33.440 --> 06:36.125
- Jesus, Carolyn.
- I wanted to surprise you.

06:36.600 --> 06:40.969
I'm sorry to tell you this, ma'am,
but you won't be receiving any prize.

06:41.120 --> 06:43.282
I'm sorry, you've been
the victim of fraud.

06:44.840 --> 06:46.046
Otis, knock it off.

06:46.200 --> 06:48.646
It's not the newest swindle
in the world.

06:48.840 --> 06:52.686
They bait you with something bogus,
then sell you something worthless.

06:52.840 --> 06:55.650
How much did you give them,
Mrs. Schaffer?

06:57.040 --> 06:59.646
Seven hundred dollars.

06:59.800 --> 07:02.644
- What's it worth?
- At any hardware store, 50 bucks.

07:02.800 --> 07:04.689
Jesus, Carolyn.

07:04.840 --> 07:06.888
We've met people
who paid twice that.

07:07.040 --> 07:08.201
- Really?
- Yeah.

07:08.400 --> 07:10.323
You wrote a check, ma'am?

07:10.480 --> 07:12.323
Did you mail it to them?

07:13.960 --> 07:15.962
No, a courier picked it up.

07:18.560 --> 07:21.166
- What?
- If they'd used the postal system...

07:21.360 --> 07:23.931
...it's mail fraud,
and we can go after them.

07:24.080 --> 07:26.651
Otherwise, there's not a lot we can do.

07:27.280 --> 07:29.647
- Unless...
- Unless what?

07:29.840 --> 07:32.002
Well, a lot of these whack jobs...

07:33.600 --> 07:37.650
...work in syndicates. If they cashed
your check out of state, it's federal.

07:37.800 --> 07:40.326
But we'd need a signed clearance
from you--

07:40.520 --> 07:43.729
I'll give you one if it will catch
these sons of bitches.

07:43.880 --> 07:46.850
- You have any more L-47s?
- Yeah, maybe in the car.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.729
Wait a second.

07:49.560 --> 07:51.244
Here we go.

07:51.400 --> 07:52.561
- Use my pen.
- I got one.

07:52.720 --> 07:54.085
