07:54.560 --> 07:56.847
- Would you let him out?
- Oh, sorry.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.130
Sorry.

08:00.600 --> 08:03.570
Here you go. That's right.

08:03.720 --> 08:05.210
Sorry.

08:08.600 --> 08:11.524
All we need is the name
of your bank...

08:12.040 --> 08:14.042
...your account number...

08:14.600 --> 08:17.490
...and your signature down below.

08:19.600 --> 08:22.729
- Any luck, these guys were amateurs...
- He all right?

08:23.560 --> 08:26.769
- ...cashed your check in Nevada.
- Sign there. You can date it.

08:29.120 --> 08:30.201
There you go.

08:31.400 --> 08:32.890
- You all right?
- He's fine.

08:33.720 --> 08:36.451
- Would you like some water?
- Everything's fine.

08:36.600 --> 08:38.328
Thank you for coming.

08:43.159 --> 08:45.401
You didn't take your pills, did you?

08:52.120 --> 08:57.047
- They left the door open. It was bitchen!
- it's just an open door, Roy.

08:58.760 --> 09:02.765
Well, it's not a fortune,
but it will keep me in diapers. Barely.

09:02.920 --> 09:06.083
Don't look at those drapes, man.
You should've known.

09:07.160 --> 09:10.642
Saw that guy again last night.
Chuck. Guy I was telling you about.

09:10.800 --> 09:13.087
- Guy with the--
- With the boat.

09:13.280 --> 09:15.760
Yeah, Frechette. Man, he's top-heavy.

09:15.920 --> 09:18.446
- Jesus Christ, what am I--?
- Don't say that.

09:18.720 --> 09:20.802
- Don't say what?
- You know what.

09:21.240 --> 09:23.447
Just don't say it.

09:26.840 --> 09:27.921
It's real money.

09:28.080 --> 09:31.129
If it's real money, it's long con.
I don't do long con.

09:31.280 --> 09:32.964
You haven't done it lately.

09:33.120 --> 09:34.804
Without me, Frank.

09:35.480 --> 09:37.209
0K8)'-

09:37.360 --> 09:41.126
I'd just like to be able to take a girl
someplace nice once in a while.

09:41.280 --> 09:43.282
You have to pay extra for that?

09:43.560 --> 09:45.961
Ha-ha-ha. Ha-ha-ha-ha.

09:49.280 --> 09:51.203
- Hi.
- Hi.

09:52.720 --> 09:56.520
Three, four, five, six and...

09:58.480 --> 10:00.960
...eight packs of Tareyton.

10:02.160 --> 10:04.561
That's 36. Out of 50.

10:04.720 --> 10:10.409
Thirty-seven, 38, 39, 40 and 10 is 50.
Thank you.

10:11.480 --> 10:12.845
Next.

11:18.160 --> 11:20.162
Mmm.

11:23.240 --> 11:24.810
Mmm.

11:37.480 --> 11:39.084
Oh, Pygmies.

11:52.800 --> 11:56.009
Mmm. Hi, this is Roy Waller calling
for Dr. Mancuso.

11:56.160 --> 11:57.241
- He moved.
- What?

11:57.440 --> 11:59.090
<i>He doesn't live here anymore, man.</i>

11:59.280 --> 12:01.328
- What do you mean, "moved"?
- He's gone.

12:01.480 --> 12:04.370
- You're shitting me. Where'd he go?
<i>- Back east.</i>

12:04.520 --> 12:06.921
- Back <i>east?
- He owes me back rent, man.</i>

12:07.120 --> 12:10.602
Give me a contact-- Hello? Hello?

12:11.920 --> 12:15.049
<i>If you'd like to make a call,
please hang up and try again.</i>

12:37.200 --> 12:40.124
Roy, it's me. It's Frankie.

12:40.320 --> 12:43.130
<i>Come on, pick it up.
I know it's tough, but come on.</i>

12:49.240 --> 12:53.484
Roy, this is Dmitri. I met you
at that club Rage the other night.

12:53.640 --> 12:55.688
<i>I really liked your leather and...</i>

12:57.000 --> 13:01.927
<i>All right, come on. Pick it up.
Pick it up. Pick it up. Pick it up.</i>

13:02.080 --> 13:03.764
Roy, come on, man. Come on.

13:05.960 --> 13:10.010
<i>Roy, it's lonely in this little office
all by myself.</i>

13:10.880 --> 13:12.928
<i>Roy, come on.</i>

13:13.520 --> 13:18.082
Roy, I wouldn't bother you, but--
Well, I'm dying, Roy.

13:18.240 --> 13:20.641
It's my spleen.

13:20.800 --> 13:24.088
I can't feel my thumbs.

13:30.640 --> 13:32.005
Hello.

13:32.800 --> 13:34.643
<i>Roy, answer the phone, man.</i>

13:34.800 --> 13:39.089
<i>I've been watching Univision all night,
and all they speak is Spanish.</i>

13:39.240 --> 13:41.368
<i>What's going on?</i>

13:42.040 --> 13:46.568
<i>But seriously, I want to talk to you
because I think I've developed a rash.</i>

13:46.760 --> 13:50.128
<i>Come on, man.
Come on, you're killing me.</i>

13:50.280 --> 13:52.851
<i>Roy, come on, what the hell?
I feel like a chick.</i>

13:54.160 --> 13:56.322
<i>All right, that's it. I'm coming over.</i>

14:07.640 --> 14:10.166
Roy? Okay, I see that.

14:10.320 --> 14:12.402
I see-- I saw you. I know you're there.

14:12.560 --> 14:14.244
Come on, Roy. Really, man.

14:14.400 --> 14:16.243
One, two, three.

14:16.760 --> 14:18.842
- Take your shoes off.
- What? Why?

14:19.240 --> 14:21.481
Take your shoes off,
or you don't come in.

14:21.640 --> 14:23.688
You didn't take your pills, did you?

14:23.880 --> 14:25.882
I'm taking them off.

14:26.040 --> 14:29.010
I'm taking the shoes off.
Give me a break over here.

14:29.160 --> 14:30.366
0K8)'-

14:30.520 --> 14:33.330
Jesus Christ.
Oh, God, what is that smell?

14:33.480 --> 14:36.450
What, did you get attacked
by Mr. Clean?

14:36.640 --> 14:39.530
- You gotta open a window, buddy.
- No! No windows.

14:39.680 --> 14:42.251
Okay. Windows are closed.
Windows are closed.

14:42.440 --> 14:44.442
You looking for something, sucker?

14:44.600 --> 14:46.602
Yeah, my partner. Have you seen him?

14:46.760 --> 14:49.445
He's been missing most of the week.
Tall guy.

14:49.720 --> 14:52.451
Hey, would you watch the rug?
You're spilling food--

14:52.920 --> 14:56.322
- You didn't take your shoes off.
- Okay, I'm taking the shoes off.

14:56.480 --> 14:58.687
I'm taking them off. See? They're off.

14:59.680 --> 15:01.489
Here you go.

15:02.520 --> 15:05.763
Oh, man, you are bad.
Did you take your pills?

15:05.960 --> 15:08.531
I spilled them down the drain
by accident.

15:08.680 --> 15:10.808
Oh, Roy, come on.
Did you call Mancuso?

15:11.000 --> 15:12.331
Moved.

15:12.480 --> 15:15.290
- You gotta be shitting me.
- That's what I said.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.562
Okay, here we go.

15:19.000 --> 15:20.650
Hurry. Come on.

15:22.800 --> 15:25.724
Come on, let's go. Come on. It's okay.

15:27.440 --> 15:30.125
I want you to breathe, okay?
Just keep breathing.

15:30.320 --> 15:31.526
Breathe. Okay.

15:31.680 --> 15:34.160
Okay. Okay, shoes are-- There you go.

15:34.320 --> 15:36.004
- You got food...
- What?

15:36.200 --> 15:41.730
Okay, food is gone.
I'm picking up all the food, okay?

15:42.160 --> 15:44.686
Listen to me, Roy. You listening?

15:44.880 --> 15:49.124
I'm gonna make a couple of calls. My
aunt saw this shrink after her divorce.

15:49.280 --> 15:52.011
- He really helped her. He's a good guy.
- Frank--

15:52.160 --> 15:55.369
You need to see someone.
Don't think I'm doing this for you.

15:55.520 --> 15:58.490
You got money. You can retire.
I got car payments, man.

15:58.680 --> 16:00.842
I don't need a partner who's like:

16:01.240 --> 16:03.720
My heart goes out to you,
but this is it now.

16:03.880 --> 16:05.928
Wipe that off when you're
done with it.

16:06.080 --> 16:09.323
Wipe the receiver. Just wipe it off.

16:09.480 --> 16:12.689
Okay. How's that? You like that?

16:12.840 --> 16:14.365
How's that?

16:14.520 --> 16:16.761
Okay, I'm sorry. Okay.

16:53.040 --> 16:56.886
Do you mind if I put them up?
It helps my back.

16:59.320 --> 17:01.163
- Go ahead.
- Thanks.

17:01.880 --> 17:04.247
Well, you're something
of a clean slate, Roy.

17:04.400 --> 17:07.290
You were on medication,
but you don't know what kind.

17:07.640 --> 17:11.201
Yeah, okay, good. Yeah,
they were these little pink tablets.

17:11.359 --> 17:14.647
I think it said "CRC" on them.
Something like that.

17:14.839 --> 17:18.083
- You were getting them illegally?
- Yes, I was. So what?

17:18.240 --> 17:21.243
- Why?
- So I wouldn't have to talk to you.

17:21.400 --> 17:23.448
- Do you know what they were?
- Yes.

17:23.640 --> 17:26.928
At that dosage,
you're lucky to be sitting up straight.

17:27.079 --> 17:29.606
That's great.
Can you get me some more of them?

17:31.800 --> 17:34.007
- You get to the point.
- And you skirt it.

17:34.160 --> 17:36.527
- Can you get me the pills or not?
- Yes.

17:36.680 --> 17:39.968
Well, then let's get
that prescription pad out.

17:40.160 --> 17:43.767
Roy, I don't prescribe medicine unless
I've chatted with the patient.

17:43.920 --> 17:47.447
If you're inclined against that,
this session will be quite brief.

18:13.120 --> 18:16.124
Would you like to tell me
what's been bothering you?

18:17.040 --> 18:21.364
I don't like being outdoors, which
I know is called "agoraphobia." Right?

18:21.520 --> 18:24.922
Incorrectly. But, yes.

18:25.120 --> 18:29.330
- Anything else?
- Dirt. Especially around moldings.

18:29.480 --> 18:32.006
I don't like when people
put shoes on my carpet.

18:32.160 --> 18:35.687
Obviously, I have a lot of tics.
I find that very frustrating.

18:36.120 --> 18:39.249
Certain things distract me,
make me feel sick to my stomach.

18:39.400 --> 18:42.688
Have these distractions
affected your work of late?

18:43.320 --> 18:45.766
And your personal relationships?

18:48.000 --> 18:49.490
What personal relationships?

18:49.640 --> 18:52.166
When was the last time
you were in one?

18:52.400 --> 18:55.768
With a woman? A long time ago.

18:55.920 --> 18:57.604
Five years?

18:58.000 --> 19:00.446
- Ten years?
- Keep going, man.

19:02.000 --> 19:03.684
What was her name?

19:06.000 --> 19:07.525
Heather.

19:08.200 --> 19:10.009
- Were you married?
- Uh-huh.

19:10.600 --> 19:11.840
Kids?

19:12.560 --> 19:14.324
Maybe.

19:14.480 --> 19:16.289
You haven't seen her since?

19:16.800 --> 19:20.566
She left me with a black eye, which
I gave her, and a bun in the oven...

19:20.760 --> 19:23.730
...which might've come from anyone.
So, no, I haven't.

19:25.720 --> 19:29.441
Look, doc, I spent last Tuesday
watching fibers on my carpet.

19:29.640 --> 19:33.770
And the whole time I was watching my
carpet, I was worrying I might vomit.

19:33.920 --> 19:37.970
I was thinking, "I'm a grown man. I
should know what goes on in my head."

19:38.120 --> 19:39.724
The more I thought about it...

19:39.880 --> 19:43.441
...the more I realized I should
blow my brains out and end it all.

19:43.600 --> 19:46.331
But if I thought more
about blowing my brains out...

19:46.480 --> 19:50.451
...I started worrying about what
that would do to my goddamn carpet.

19:51.560 --> 19:53.085
So that was a good day, doc.

19:53.240 --> 19:57.962
And I just want you to give me some
pills and let me get on with my life.

20:07.800 --> 20:09.131
Uh-huh.

20:09.280 --> 20:11.248
- Roy.
- What?

20:11.400 --> 20:13.528
He just gave them to you at the office?

20:13.680 --> 20:16.809
He said they were new.
Prefex something-or-other.

20:16.960 --> 20:19.042
- You feel better?
- A little.

20:19.200 --> 20:20.804
You want to work soon?

20:23.080 --> 20:24.809
Think you can you control the...?

20:24.960 --> 20:27.327
- What?
- Nothing.

20:44.240 --> 20:47.369
- What <i>city, please?</i>
- Woodland Hills, California.

20:47.520 --> 20:49.761
- Name, <i>sir?</i>
- Fenton, Heather.

20:49.920 --> 20:52.651
- Can you <i>spell that?</i>
- F-E-N--

21:17.360 --> 21:21.843
<i>If that's you, then this is me.
So leave a message after the beep.</i>

21:23.000 --> 21:25.048
- Hello, this is--
- <i>Hello?</i>

21:28.560 --> 21:31.689
Well, you know, we fought a lot.

21:31.840 --> 21:33.649
- About what?
- What do you got?

21:33.800 --> 21:35.370
I wasn't sober a lot then.

21:35.800 --> 21:37.643
Are you now?

21:37.800 --> 21:40.246
So some nights,
she just didn't come home.

21:40.440 --> 21:44.729
She was pregnant two months
before she even told me about it.

21:46.280 --> 21:48.521
Yeah. Do you think about her much?

21:48.680 --> 21:52.002
You know, what could have been,
what might have been.

21:53.680 --> 21:56.570
- And the baby?
- If there's a baby.

21:57.120 --> 22:00.124
- Do you think about that?
- Sometimes. Rarely.

22:00.280 --> 22:05.889
Like, if I see a school bus, I'll wonder,
"ls one of those kids Roy Jr?"

22:06.040 --> 22:10.090
He, if he's a he, would be how old now?

22:11.280 --> 22:14.250
He'd be 14.

22:15.560 --> 22:17.130
Fourteen, ready to be a man.

22:18.960 --> 22:22.203
Yeah. If he's a he.

22:22.400 --> 22:24.402
If he is at all.

22:31.040 --> 22:34.931
Congratulations.
You bought yourself a week's worth.

22:35.120 --> 22:36.724
Thanks.

22:38.080 --> 22:39.764
Listen, doc...

22:39.960 --> 22:43.521
...do you know of a way...

22:43.680 --> 22:46.206
...just to find out, you know...

22:46.360 --> 22:49.330
There's nothing wrong
with a man telephoning his ex-wife.

22:49.480 --> 22:52.404
I tried that last night,
and I couldn't say a word.

22:52.560 --> 22:54.847
So could you call her?

22:55.760 --> 22:59.287
- I don't know, Roy. I--
- Please. It's just to find out.

23:04.920 --> 23:07.287
- Now?
- No, after I'm gone.

23:07.800 --> 23:09.928
When you can.

23:12.200 --> 23:13.850
- Okay.
- That's great.

23:14.800 --> 23:16.450
